ysis\n     2\t\n     3\t**Author:** Dave (Full Stack Engineer)  \n     4\t**Date
:** 2026-04-01  \n     5\t**Task:** 240 ŌĆö Fix CoinGecko rate limit causing Crypt
oEdgeStrategy failures\n     6\t\n     7\t---\n     8\t\n     9\t## Problem\n   
10\t\n    11\t`crypto_edge_analysis.py` was hitting CoinGecko's rate limit (HTTP
429) when the pipeline ran `live_runner.js` multiple times in quick succession. 
Without caching, every strategy execution triggered a fresh CoinGecko API call.\
n    12\t\n    13\t## Changes Made\n    14\t\n    15\t### 1. File-Based Caching 
(`crypto_edge_analysis.py`)\n    16\t\n    17\tAdded a `.coingecko_cache.json` f
ile with a **5-minute TTL**:\n    18\t\n    19\t- `get_cached_prices()` ŌĆö reads 
cache if it exists and is still fresh\n    20\t- `save_prices_to_cache(prices)` 
ŌĆö writes cache after a successful API call\n    21\t- Cache location: `output/.c
oingecko_cache.json` (same directory as the script)\n    22\t\n    23\t### 2. Ex
ponential Backoff Retry\n    24\t\n    25\tReplaced the simple retry loop with `
fetch_prices_with_retry()`:\n    26\t\n    27\t- **Max retries:** 3\n    28\t- *
*Base delay:** 2 seconds\n    29\t- **Backoff:** `delay = base_delay * (2 ** att
empt)`\n    30\t- **429 handling:** Detects rate-limit status code explicitly, s
leeps, then retries\n    31\t- **Network errors:** Catches `requests.exceptions.
RequestException` and retries\n    32\t\n    33\t### 3. Integration with Existin
g Flow\n    34\t\n    35\t`fetch_crypto_prices()` now:\n    36\t1. Checks cache 
first\n    37\t2. If cache miss, calls `fetch_prices_with_retry()`\n    38\t3. S
aves successful API response to cache\n    39\t4. Returns parsed BTC/ETH prices\
n    40\t\n    41\tThe `--json` flag behavior is unchanged ŌĆö JSON signals are st
ill emitted at the end of stdout for `crypto_edge.js` consumption.\n    42\t\n  
 43\t## Test Results\n    44\t\n    45\t### Run 1 (Cache Miss)\n    46\t\n    47
\t```\n    48\t[1/4] Fetching live BTC/ETH prices from CoinGecko...\n    49\t   
  BTC: $66,560.00\n    50\t      ETH: $2,046.81\n    51\t```\n    52\t\n    53\t
Cache file created: `output/.coingecko_cache.json`\n    54\t\n    55\t### Run 2 
(Cache Hit)\n    56\t\n    57\t```\n    58\t[1/4] Fetching live BTC/ETH prices f
rom CoinGecko...\n    59\t[CoinGecko] Using cached prices.\n    60\t      BTC: $
66,560.00\n    61\t      ETH: $2,046.81\n    62\t```\n    63\t\n    64\tŌ£ģ Secon
d run used cached prices ŌĆö no CoinGecko API call.\n    65\t\n    66\t### JSON Ou
tput Verification\n    67\t\n    68\t```bash\n    69\tpython output/crypto_edge_
analysis.py --json\n    70\t```\n    71\t\n    72\tOutput: 7 valid signals, JSON
parseable by `crypto_edge.js`.\n    73\t\n    74\t## Impact\n    75\t\n    76\t-
**Before:** Every pipeline run hit CoinGecko ŌåÆ 429 errors after 2-3 runs\n    77
\t- **After:** Only 1 API call every 5 minutes ŌåÆ pipeline runs are stable and fa
